    How many inches is a large claw clip?
    Hair Clip Sizes: Small, Medium & Large Claw Clips Compared
    Clip SizeAverage LengthBest For
    Basic (Small)3 inches (7.5 cm)Fine, thin or short hair
    Next Level (Medium)4 inches (10 cm)Medium to thick hair
    Extra XL (Large)5 inches (12.5 cm)Thick, long, or voluminous hair

    Are claw clips damaging to hair?
    We've established that claw clips aren't bad for your hair per se, but wearing the wrong type of claw clip and rocking it too frequently are what can cause hair damage.

    What is the difference between small and large claw clips?
    Large Claw Clips: These clips are perfect for thick, long hair and can easily hold up voluminous updos or ponytails. Small Claw Clips: Ideal for shorter hair or for securing smaller sections, small claw clips are versatile and can be used to create half-up half-down styles or to pin back bangs.
